The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring September 17 as Constitution Day and Citizenship Day, and September 17 through September 23 as Constitution Week. The proclamation highlights the importance of the Constitution and the responsibilities of citizenship in the United States. It emphasizes the history of the Constitution and how it has inspired nations and immigrants to seek freedom and prosperity. The proclamation calls for ceremonies and programs to reflect on active citizenship and reaffirm commitment to the rights and obligations of citizenship.